      {
        "id": 2340635,
        "name": "Stephen Williams",
        "username": "Stephen_Williams",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/s/57b2e6/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-01-21T14:26:05.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The Clos du Cailleret was bought by some Asian based investors with Ramonet contracted to make the wine.  It\u2019s superb, as are the two new St Abin.</p>\n<p>I drank a 2000 Chevy yesterday.  More often than not, it has underwhelmed relatively speaking, among his 4 GC but this bottle was absolutely singing.  A beautiful colour, lovely racy palate.  Better 24 hours later.</p>\n<p>Value wise, it\u2019s priced a fraction behind the Montrachet, which I suppose is due to rarity.  I much prefer the BM and BBM at 60% the price or the Monty at \u20ac20 more</p>",
        "post_number": 7,
